{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770137781,"nonce":"mSsIC1jixrGp3TSxdziusI2mn4k=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87n_qM5","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/149","origin":"github"},"title":"Implement review-against-rules workflow","message":"## Summary\n\nImplement a workflow that reviews completed work against workspace guidelines and rules, inspired by Conductor's `/conductor:review` command.\n\n## Parent Issue\n\nSub-issue of #139\n\n## Motivation\n\nConductor provides a `/conductor:review` command that reviews completed work against guidelines and the plan. This helps catch issues before PR submission and ensures consistency. Our workspace should have an equivalent capability that works with all agent frameworks.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### Create Review Script\n\n**File**: `.agent/scripts/review_against_rules.sh`\n\n```bash\n# Review completed work against workspace guidelines\n#\n# Usage: \n#   review_against_rules.sh --pr \u003cnumber\u003e\n#   review_against_rules.sh --branch \u003cbranch-name\u003e\n```\n\n### What It Checks\n\n| Check | Rule Source | Severity |\n|-------|-------------|----------|\n| AI signature in PR body | `.agent/rules/common/ai-signature.md` | Error |\n| Issue referenced in commits | `.agent/rules/common/issue-first.md` | Warning |\n| Branch naming convention | `.agent/rules/common/git-hygiene.md` | Warning |\n| CHANGELOG updated | `CONTRIBUTING.md` | Warning (if code changes) |\n| No commits to protected paths | `.agent/PERMISSIONS.md` | Error |\n| Tests added for code changes | `.agent/rules/definition-of-done.md` | Warning |\n| No build artifacts committed | `.agent/rules/common/clean-root.md` | Error |\n\n### Output Format\n\nMarkdown report suitable for:\n- Terminal display\n- PR comment\n- Scratchpad file\n\nExample output:\n```markdown\n## Review Report: PR #146\n\n### ✅ Passed (5)\n- AI signature present\n- Issue #139 referenced\n- Branch naming: feature/issue-139 ✓\n- No protected path violations\n- No build artifacts\n\n### ⚠️ Warnings (1)\n- Tests: No test file found for .agent/scripts/revert_feature.sh\n\n### ❌ Errors (0)\n\n**Overall**: Ready for review with minor suggestions\n```\n\n## Integration\n\n- [ ] Add to `CLI_COMMANDS.md` as `/review-pr`\n- [ ] Add Makefile target: `make review-pr PR=\u003cnumber\u003e`\n- [ ] Document in `CONTRIBUTING.md`\n- [ ] Consider GitHub Action for automated PR checks (future)\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Script\n- [ ] Create `.agent/scripts/review_against_rules.sh`\n- [ ] Implement PR metadata checks (signature, issue reference)\n- [ ] Implement branch naming check\n- [ ] Implement protected path check\n- [ ] Generate markdown report\n\n### Phase 2: Integration\n- [ ] Add to CLI_COMMANDS.md\n- [ ] Add Makefile target\n- [ ] Add tests for the script\n\n### Phase 3: Documentation\n- [ ] Update CONTRIBUTING.md with review workflow\n- [ ] Add examples to agent onboarding docs\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Script runs successfully on open PRs\n- [ ] Report clearly shows pass/warn/fail status\n- [ ] Output is valid markdown\n- [ ] Integrates with existing CLI command discovery\n- [ ] Works with all agent frameworks (no IDE dependencies)\n\n## Effort Estimate\n\n**Medium** (3-4 hours)\n\n## Related\n\n- Conductor `/conductor:review` command for reference\n- #139 - Parent issue\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Claude Opus 4.5`","files":null}]}